      "description": "The activation sequence is identical for every invocation: full greeting, full 14-item capabilities table, stop-and-wait. A first-timer sees 14 cryptic codes with no recommended starting path. An expert who has used Ferris 100 times sees the same ceremony. A confused user has no visible exit. The Overview provides no domain framing for a new-session LLM.",
      "severity": "high",
      "impact": "Fixing this transforms the user experience for all three primary segments (first-timer, expert, confused). Reduces time-to-action for experts, reduces confusion for newcomers, and eliminates the trapped-in-persona problem.",
      "action": "Introduce context-aware activation: detect first-run state from forge-tier.yaml (tier: ~), check compact_greeting preference for returning users, add exit/dismiss option to capabilities table footer, and expand Overview to 4-6 sentences with domain framing.",
      "finding_count": 8,
      "findings": [
        {
          "title": "No guided first-run experience — first-timer faces blank menu",
