        {
          "title": "Repetitive activation ceremony for returning users",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 64,
          "detail": "Every activation plays the full greeting + capabilities table + stop-and-wait regardless of whether the user has used Ferris 100 times.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "No exit/dismiss guidance in capabilities table",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 36,
          "detail": "The SKILL.md states 'you must not break character until the user dismisses this persona' but never tells the user how to dismiss Ferris.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Under-contextualized Overview for a complex interactive agent",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 9,
          "detail": "The Overview is a single compound sentence that reads more like a capabilities summary than a mental model. No domain framing, theory of mind, or success criteria.",
          "source": "prompt-craft"
        },
        {
          "title": "Three-Mode Architecture not present but conceptually aligned",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 14,
          "detail": "The five identity modes hint at flexibility but the activation pattern does not adapt to user experience level (Guided/Yolo/Autonomous).",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Soft Gate Elicitation only partially present",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 75,
          "detail": "The forger uses hard menu gates exclusively. A softer initial 'What are you looking to do today?' before the full table would improve discovery.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Table row numbering for 'number' input method undocumented",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 75,
          "detail": "CRITICAL Handling says 'Accept number, menu code, or fuzzy command match' but the capabilities table does not have row numbers.",
          "source": "skill-cohesion"
        },
        {
          "title": "No 'Where Was I?' resumption after interruption",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 64,
          "detail": "If a session ends mid-workflow, there is no way to resume. Sidecar tracks tier and preferences but not workflow progress.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Lifecycle Knowledge is Powerful but Invisible",
      "description": "The knowledge system (15 cross-cutting fragments, CSV index, JiT loading) contains high-value lifecycle guidance including five named 'Typical Flows.' But this knowledge is behind two layers of indirection (KI code -> CSV -> fragment). Cross-capability chaining is documented but not operationalized.",
      "severity": "medium",
      "impact": "Proactive knowledge surfacing transforms the experience from 'pick from 14 options' to 'here is your recommended path.' Pipeline chaining operationalizes the lifecycle vision documented in the knowledge artifacts.",
      "action": "Surface the most relevant knowledge fragment proactively at key moments (first-run: typical flows; post-workflow: suggested next step). Support pipeline invocation syntax that validates chains against lifecycle artifacts.",
      "finding_count": 5,
      "findings": [
        {
          "title": "Knowledge index is invisible to users",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 80,
          "detail": "The knowledge system is accessed via the KI code, listed alongside 13 other options with no special prominence. Users who don't know knowledge exists will never ask for it.",
