          "source": "skill-cohesion"
        },
        {
          "title": "Docs-only skills not visible in forger menu",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 40,
          "detail": "Brief-skill supports source_type: docs-only but the forger's BS description does not mention docs-only support. Users with only documentation URLs might not realize Skill Forge can help.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Deterministic Activation Work Performed by the LLM",
      "description": "On every activation, the LLM parses YAML config, validates a filesystem path, loads two sidecar YAML files, and (on KI invocation) parses a CSV index. All are deterministic operations costing an estimated 500-850 tokens per activation cycle with parsing variance risk.",
      "severity": "medium",
      "impact": "Script-based pre-flight makes activation deterministic and instant, saves 500-850 tokens per invocation, and provides reusable config validation for all SKF skills.",
      "action": "Create skf-preflight.py (loads config.yaml, validates sidecar_path, loads preferences.yaml and forge-tier.yaml, outputs JSON) and skf-knowledge-query.py (accepts topic, returns matching fragments from CSV index). Both reusable across SKF skills.",
      "finding_count": 5,
      "findings": [
        {
          "title": "Config loading and variable resolution is deterministic YAML extraction",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 66,
          "detail": "LLM parses config.yaml and resolves eight named variables on every activation. Pure key-value extraction.",
          "source": "script-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Sidecar path validation is a filesystem existence check",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 57,
          "detail": "The GUARD instructs the LLM to verify a directory exists — a deterministic filesystem check that needs zero LLM involvement.",
          "source": "script-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Sidecar file loading is mechanical YAML reading",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 58,
          "detail": "Loading preferences.yaml and forge-tier.yaml is deterministic file reading that a script could pre-parse into JSON.",
          "source": "script-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Knowledge index CSV query is deterministic parsing",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 61,
          "detail": "CSV parsing and keyword matching against fragment descriptions is entirely deterministic. Script could return ranked fragment list.",
          "source": "script-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Sequential config/state loading could be batched",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 58,
          "detail": "preferences.yaml and forge-tier.yaml are independent reads that could be parallel-loaded in a single message after the sidecar_path guard passes.",
          "source": "execution-efficiency"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Missing Error Handling for Non-Sidecar Failures",
      "description": "The sidecar_path GUARD is exemplary defensive design. But it is the only guard. Config.yaml missing, delegated workflow failure, missing knowledge CSV, and context compaction in long sessions are all unhandled failure modes.",
      "severity": "medium",
      "impact": "Completing the defensive pattern makes the skill resilient across the full range of failure modes, not just the sidecar case. Users in hostile environments get actionable guidance instead of undefined behavior.",
      "action": "Add parallel guards for config.yaml existence and knowledge CSV availability. Add a 2-3 sentence error-recovery section for returning from failed workflows. Document inline action fallbacks for missing files.",
      "finding_count": 4,
      "findings": [
        {
          "title": "Missing config.yaml fallback",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 66,
          "detail": "If config.yaml does not exist (fresh clone, misconfigured install), the activation behavior is undefined. No actionable guidance.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "No error recovery protocol for failed child workflows",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 77,
          "detail": "If a delegated workflow fails or is interrupted, there is no guidance for what state the hub should be in or what to present to the user.",
          "source": "skill-cohesion"
        },
        {
          "title": "Inline actions (KI, WS) have no error handling",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 80,
          "detail": "Neither KI nor WS specifies what happens if underlying files are missing, malformed, or empty. Inconsistent with the guard-first pattern.",
          "source": "enhancement-opportunities"
        },
        {
          "title": "Context compaction vulnerability in long sessions",
          "file": "SKILL.md",
          "line": 30,
